<br>
And often the higher lv you get.. the more arrongant you get in fear.. you start to think of it as a 'trivial' encounter.. then before you know it 6 scarlings have just eaten your main cleric and enchanter, shiverbacks are beating on the fighers and along comes a tenticle terror dispelling your buffs.. a few turmoil toads fearing you.... all of a sudden al clerics are dead, melee are wounded the druids trys to heal and gets agro and dies... tanks are to scared to taunt so they get eaten one by one because no damage shareing...... i've seen the 'highest' lv guilds on my old server die to this... seen them die again and again on there recovery, seen the next highest guild on the served die getting the other guild out... then seen 4 peope lead an open raid and res them all up.<br>
<br>
Fear is great fun.. one of the only places you can count as a 'trivial' plane yet really underneeth it all.. there's a beast waiting to get it's revenge.. be afraid.. very afraid.<br>
<br>
