<br>
Quick little secret -- when players are not harping on loot and exp -- raids are NOT hard to run.  When players join the leadership channel and actually LEAD -- raids are not hard to run. <br>
<br>
When players try hard and make honest -- not stupid -- mistakes  --  Raids are not hard to run.  When players bring raid supplies (peridots) and realize that they may not be reimbursed this time -- Raids are not hard to run.<br>
<br>
I do not expect folks to hit every raid -- and over two-thirds of sign-ups actually CAME on the FEAR raid.  The whole community helps out the OPEN RAID CONCEPT.  Bless you all ).<br>
<br>
Gbuffy -- Fashion Consultant<br>
Dressed in Ninja-looted Finery<br>
Has not made a level in over three months<br>
